    "section_custom_content_AyDzny": {
      "type": "section-custom-content",
      "blocks": {
        "text_Jikqa8": {
          "type": "text",
          "settings": {
            "subheading": "Re-Introducing:",
            "title": "TEST",
            "heading_font_size": "heading-large",
            "text": "<p>One of the most sustainable things we can do? <strong>Use what already exists.</strong> That’s the concept behind Special Projects—limited-run garments made from premium deadstock fabrics, cut and sewn in California. When they're gone, they're gone. </p><p>Some of our most beloved pieces (remember that decadent merino? Or the original microgrid?) were born this way. It’s a sustainability win, a creative constraint, and a chance to make something out of something forgotten. </p>",
            "text_font_size": "body-small",
            "button_text": "Latest Special Projects",
            "button_url": "shopify://collections/special-projects",
            "button_type": "btn--primary",
